{"session_id": 45, "bill_id": 12372, "bill_type": "Senate Bill", "bill_number": 5, "bill_title": "to make certain large-scale contract livestock feeders liable for environmental damages.", "sponsors": [{"legislator_profile_id": 1939, "is_prime": true}, {"legislator_profile_id": 1954, "is_prime": true}, {"legislator_profile_id": 1897, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 1926, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 1930, "is_prime": false}, {"legislator_profile_id": 1932, "is_prime": false}], "keywords": ["Hog Farms", "Torts, Liabilities & Damages", "Water Pollution"], "audio": [], "bill_versions": [{"bill_id": 12372, "bill_version_id": 74082, "bill_version": "Introduced", "bill_version_date": "1996-12-24T00:00:00-06:00", "bill_text": "FOR AN ACT ENTITLED, An Act to make certain large-scale contract livestock feeders liable for environmental damages. BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA: Section 1. The owner of any livestock animals that are bred, farrowed, fed, or raised on a contractual basis on property not owned by the livestock owner is liable for any damage or pollution to the environment or the waters of the state resulting from such activity if the livestock owner is not a family farm as defined in \u00a7 47-9A-2, a family farm corporation as defined in \u00a7 47-9A-14, or an authorized farm corporation as defined in \u00a7 47-9A-15 and if the contract specifies design, construction, or operations standards or requirements that apply to the property or facilities where such activity occurs. This section does not exempt the owner of the property on which any livestock animals are bred, farrowed, fed, or raised from liability for such damage or pollution. 750 copies of this document were printed by the South Dakota Legislative Research Council at a cost of $.015 per page. . Insertions into existing statutes are indicated by underscores. Deletions from existing statutes are indicated by overstrikes."}], "amendments": [], 